<p style="text-align:justify;">Husbands makes them believe whatever they please, <span class="AddHand-editors">[a]</span>nd that by Virtue of this Bag, they will Know whenever their Wives proves unfaithfull to them or misbeh<span class="AddHand-editors">[a]</span>ves in any thing Else &#8211; for which reason they are in general pretty Chaste when Sober, but when the least in Liquor, they Indulge themselves with such sport as Comes in their way, and if found Out upon them, <span class="AddHand-editors">[th]</span>ey will say that they remember nothing of it, and <span class="AddHand-editors">[wa]</span>s Senseless at the time; so that was not them <span class="AddHand-editors">[that]</span> misbehaved, but the Liquor<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>herefore a Woman <span class="AddHand-editors">[is]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[ne]</span>ver reckoned a whore for what she does when <span class="AddHand-editors">[inebr]</span>iated, provided She was never Known to misbe<span class="AddHand-editors">[hav]</span>e when Sober, in which State She <span class="AddHand-author">will</span> not Even fa<span class="AddHand-editors">[vo]</span>ur, her favorite gallant<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
